      • deviceUpdateCallbackInterval

        GeneralConfigurator deviceUpdateCallbackInterval(long intervalInMillis)
        The device update callback interval prevents the update from being called instantly.
        Once the Android device enters a space with many BLE devices the update event starts to be called with instantly growing number of updated BLE devices.
        This may cause interruptions when interacting with UI. The device update callback interval option causes the update callback to be invoked no more often than given interval. Default: 3000 milliseconds.
        Parameters:
        intervalInMillis - Interval in milliseconds.
        Returns:
        GeneralConfigurator builder

      • eddystoneFrameTypes

        GeneralConfigurator eddystoneFrameTypes(java.util.Collection<EddystoneFrameType> eddystoneFrameTypes)
        Sets trigger frame types. The trigger frame types specify with which frame types received at least the Eddystone device should be notified.
        If not set Eddystone device will be notified as soon as any frame will be scanned (UID, URL or TLM).
        Parameters:
        eddystoneFrameTypes - eddystone format frame types
        Returns:
        GeneralConfigurator builder
